key_insights: Leverage in Bitcoin (10X-100X) can lead to catastrophic liquidations - when BTC drops 10%, leveraged accounts can be wiped out completely
Options limit risk to cost of trade, unlike leverage which can create debt beyond initial investment
When Bitcoin sells off hard, leveraged traders must liquidate regular stocks (AAPL, GOOGL, META, MSFT) to cover losses
$1.2 trillion was liquidated out of Bitcoin during this crash
Gap fills happen 80-90% of the time once a stock enters the gap on daily timeframe
Use Fibonacci retracements with price levels for confluence - SPY rejected exactly in the golden zone (50-61.8%)
Market pushed higher after Nvidia earnings on Thursday, then relentless selling all day - this is structural damage
Don't trade on Friday after Thanksgiving - low volume, lots of chop, poor risk/reward ratio
Safety buying moved to banks, airlines, oil, pharma rather than technology during selloff
When market loses key support levels (like BTC at 107k), it triggers cascade of liquidations

notable_events: Thanksgiving week - market closed Thursday, early close Friday 1pm ET
Key earnings: Zoom, Dell, Alibaba, Coles, Best Buy
Government shutdown ended, economic data stream resuming

Home prices dropping, cheaper than new construction

summary: Bill Fanter provides a comprehensive market watchlist for Thanksgiving week, explaining how Bitcoin's leveraged liquidation cascade ($1.2T wiped out) forced selling in major tech stocks. He emphasizes the dangers of leverage versus options trading, analyzes key support/resistance levels across major indices and individual stocks using Fibonacci retracements and gap theory, and advises against trading the low-volume Friday after Thanksgiving. The overall market shows structural damage with bearish pressure, though some opportunities exist in oversold names like META.
